  "texts": [
    "The subject is in the kitchen.",
    "Here, the pantry drawer is already open.",
    "After 2 seconds, they close the pantry drawer.We observe that in this case, ADL-LLM takes into consideration the fact that the stove is one of the monitored appliances (even if not used by the subject in the current window) to correctly predict the \"preparing a cold meal\" activity.",
    "Indeed, the LLM motivated that the current activity can not be preparing a hot meal with the following argument: \"[...] Preparing hot meal: This could involve using ingredients from the pantry, but we don't have evidence of cooking or using the stove.",
    "[...]\" On the other hand, if the environment's description is omitted, the response to the same input becomes:[...] Since the pantry is typically used for storing food items, and the subject's action of closing the drawer implies they were likely preparing something, the most fitting activity is 'preparing hot meal' or 'preparing cold meal'."
  ],
